quran[9]{c,v,t}:
  70,36,"So, what is the matter with the unbelievers that they rush madly before you—"
  70,37,From the right and from the left in crowds
  70,38,Does every man from them wish to enter the Paradise (and the Garden of Joy)
  70,39,"Definitely no! Verily, We have created them out of the (base matter) they know"
  70,40,"But now, I swear by the Lord of (every point in) the Easts' and the Wests' that We can certainly—"
  70,41,Substitute them by others better (men) than them; And We are not to be defeated (in Our Plan)
  70,42,"So, leave them to sink in idle talk and play about— Until they encounter that Day of theirs that they have been promised"
  70,43,The Day when they will come out of from their graves in sudden haste as if they were rushing to a goal-post (fixed for them)—
  70,44,With their eyes lowered in sadness— Fear and shame covering them (all over)! That is the Day that they were promised